'''生命之樹'''（{{lang-es|Árboles de la Vida}}）是一系列位於[[尼加拉瓜|尼加拉瓜]]首都[[馬拿瓜|馬拿瓜]]的[[裝置藝術|裝置藝術]]，最初在2013年，為紀念[[尼加拉瓜革命|尼加拉瓜革命]]34周年而建造<ref name="Mallonee 2018">{{Cite news|url=https://hyperallergic.com/117612/psychedelic-symbols-of-state-power-in-nicaragua/|title=Psychedelic Symbols of State Power in Nicaragua|last=Mallonee|first=Laura C.|date=2014-03-31|work=Hyperallergic|access-date=2018-05-11|language=en-US|archive-date=2018-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180512181638/https://hyperallergic.com/117612/psychedelic-symbols-of-state-power-in-nicaragua/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。生命之樹是由尼加拉瓜第一夫人{{le|罗莎里奥·穆里欧|Rosario Murillo}}（2017年起擔任副總統）主導的城市美化工程的其中一部份。

==裝置藝術==
生命之樹由大約140座抽象、色彩鮮艷的抽象[[樹|樹]]形雕塑組成，散佈在馬拿瓜的各處街道中；其造型是以[[奧地利|奧地利]]知名[[象徵主義|象徵主義]]畫家[[古斯塔夫·克林姆|古斯塔夫·克林姆]]的作品《{{link-en|生命之樹 (畫作)|The Tree of Life, Stoclet Frieze|生命之樹}}》（''L'Arbre de Vie, Stoclet Frieze''）的啟發<ref name="Mallonee 2018" />。這些『樹』由金屬製成，總共用250萬個微型燈泡裝飾<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rogers|first1=Tim|title=Nicaragua's capital city is batshit crazy, which is why I love it|url=https://splinternews.com/nicaraguas-capital-city-is-batshit-crazy-which-is-why-1793853419|accessdate=10 May 2018|work=Splinter|date=December 8, 2015|archive-date=2018-05-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180511150254/https://splinternews.com/nicaraguas-capital-city-is-batshit-crazy-which-is-why-1793853419|dead-url=no}}</ref>，每座的高度約為12到17米高，每座的成本據稱為20,000美元25,000美元<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wilkinson|first1=Tracy|title=Nicaragua's first lady is a powerful partner of president|url=http://www.latimes.com/world/mexico-americas/la-fg-nicaragua-trees-20150524-story.html|accessdate=10 May 2018|work=Los Angeles Times|date=May 24, 2015|archive-date=2021-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211108230431/https://www.latimes.com/world/mexico-americas/la-fg-nicaragua-trees-20150524-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[2018－2020年尼加拉瓜示威|2018－2020年尼加拉瓜示威]]中，部分裝置藝術作品被焚毀，這些舉動被視為對政府及穆里欧的譴責<ref name="Phillips 2018">{{cite news|last1=Phillips|first1=Tom|title=Nicaragua's toppling 'trees' strike ominous note for Daniel Ortega's rule|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/apr/28/nicaragua-daniel-ortega-trees-of-life-protests|accessdate=11 May 2018|work=The Guardian|date=28 April 2018|language=en|archive-date=2018-05-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180511150242/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/apr/28/nicaragua-daniel-ortega-trees-of-life-protests|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2018/04/22/604762080/violent-unrest-continues-in-nicaragua-over-social-security-reforms|title=Nicaragua's President Withdraws Social Security Reforms That Sparked Violent Unrest|last=Diao|first=Alexis|date=April 22, 2018|work=NPR.org|access-date=2018-05-11|language=en|archive-date=2018-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180422210743/https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2018/04/22/604762080/violent-unrest-continues-in-nicaragua-over-social-security-reforms|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

